03/18/76  login, l

Function:  used to gain access to the Multics system.

Syntax:  login Person_id {-control_args}


Arguments:  Person_id is the user's registered personal identifier.


Control arguments:
-brief, -bf  suppress messages associated with successful login.
-change_password, -cpw  change user's password; give old password in
 normal manner first.
-no_print_off, -npf  overtype string of characters to provide black
 area for user's password.
-terminal_type XX, -ttp XX  set user's terminal type to XX, where XX
 is one of the types listed for the same control argument of the
 set_tty command.
-modes XX  set modes for terminal I/O according to XX, where XX is
 one of the modes listed for the same control argument of the set_tty
 command.
